Step 1: Identify the operating cash flow from the cash flow statement.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -6,856,840.58

Step 2: Identify the total current liabilities from the balance sheet.  
• Total Current Liabilities = 1,601,835.08

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio:  
 Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)  
  = -6,856,840.58 / 1,601,835.08  
  ≈ -4.28

Thus, the operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio is approximately -4.28.
